The paper deals with topological data analysis, which involves analyzing data sets using tools from algebraic topology. This makes it likely to fall under the category of Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for approximating the persistent homology of Rips filtrations, which involves manipulating and analyzing large amounts of data, making it relevant to the sub-categories of Data Mining (cs.DM) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the limitations of existing approaches and proposes a new strategy, which involves optimizing the efficiency of the algorithm, making it relevant to the sub-category of Scientific Computing (cs.SI).
